description:
&lt;p&gt;An opportunity has arisen to join a friendly, proactive Dietetic service with an excellent reputation for its work in both the hospital and community setting. &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful candidates will be part of the band 5 rotation within our acute team.  The post holder will provide a service to in-patients and out-patients clinics based at Leighton Hospital. This post offers the opportunity for a newly qualified dietitian to develop their clinical skills within a variety of areas including medicine, orthopaedics and surgery and also for a band 5 dietitian to develop their skills in specialist areas as part of the rotational element of the post. The team includes specialist dietitians for adult stroke, gastroenterology, surgery, diabetes, paediatrics and critical care and there will be opportunities for further clinical development within these specialist fields.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Regular huddle meetings support clinical practice and workload management, alongside your clinical mentor promoting advancement of your clinical skills and confidence.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our service is committed to the training of student dietitians and other health care professionals. The post holder will be involved in on-going staff training in nutritional screening across the acute unit and patient education for the cardiac rehabilitation services in the community. The service is developing virtual training and videos to support education and training and utilising IT facilities to enhance patient care &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The department encourages innovation and supports continuous professional development. We have excellent IT facilities and secretarial support.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post is subject to an enhanced Disclosure and Barring service check&lt;/p&gt;
